1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,980
I Want You to Make This Cat Purr, Meow.

2
00:00:00,860 --> 00:00:03,780
I want you to make this cat purr, meow.

3
00:00:06,530 --> 00:00:08,220
By the way, Shirota-kun.

4
00:00:08,220 --> 00:00:10,320
Did you finish the assignments 
we have to hand in today?

5
00:00:10,320 --> 00:00:14,280
Huh? I thought we could hand
 those in after summer break?

6
00:00:14,790 --> 00:00:18,000
Looks like your summer break 
will be taken up by supplementary lessons.

7
00:00:18,000 --> 00:00:19,710
You're joking, right?

8
00:00:19,710 --> 00:00:23,880
I feel bad for the teachers who'll be 
forced to give you extra lessons

9
00:00:23,880 --> 00:00:26,110
instead of enjoying their summer break.

10
00:00:27,060 --> 00:00:30,860
I suppose I can find it in my heart 
to help you during lunch break.

11
00:00:30,860 --> 00:00:31,880
Really?

12
00:00:32,900 --> 00:00:36,130
However, you will have to turn 
on the spot three times and proclaim,

13
00:00:36,130 --> 00:00:41,100
"I'll become Takamine-sama's slave and 
dedicate the rest of my life to her, woof."

14
00:00:41,750 --> 00:00:42,590
While completely naked.

15
00:00:42,590 --> 00:00:43,890
Why, though?!

16
00:00:43,890 --> 00:00:47,220
Well, I guess since you have all Cs,

17
00:00:43,890 --> 00:00:50,400
<i></i><i>Mandatory 
Subjects
 </i><i>
Math II: C
 
Science: C
 Art: C</i>

18
00:00:47,220 --> 00:00:50,400
not handing them in would probably 
only knock you down to all Ds.

19
00:00:50,760 --> 00:00:52,960
That might be true,

20
00:00:53,460 --> 00:00:57,970
but if I secretly work on them 
during class and all the breaks,

21
00:00:57,970 --> 00:01:00,820
I can get them done... I think.

22
00:01:00,820 --> 00:01:03,160
So I think I'll try it on my own.

23
00:01:04,870 --> 00:01:08,050
Could it be that you learned 
what it's like to try hard

24
00:01:08,050 --> 00:01:11,520
and achieve something 
during that running training?

25
00:01:11,520 --> 00:01:13,930
Uh, well, kinda.

26
00:01:14,660 --> 00:01:21,250
So you're saying I have accidentally trained 
you to awaken to a new kind of pleasure.

27
00:01:21,250 --> 00:01:23,430
Why did you rephrase it like that?!

28
00:01:23,940 --> 00:01:26,390
Well, just give it your best,

29
00:01:27,230 --> 00:01:31,300
but don't neglect your duties as my closet.

30
00:01:31,300 --> 00:01:32,590
Oh, sure.

31
00:01:33,630 --> 00:01:35,570
<i>With that said,</i>

32
00:01:35,570 --> 00:01:38,920
<i>I don't know if I can finish these assignments
 just by working on them on the side.</i>

33
00:01:38,920 --> 00:01:42,450
<i>President also uses her power 
up to 10 times on an intense day,</i>

34
00:01:41,860 --> 00:01:44,540
Okay, Takamine, do this question.

35
00:01:42,450 --> 00:01:44,540
<i>so that means I'll need time 
to put something on her...</i>

36
00:01:44,540 --> 00:01:45,540
Yes.

37
00:01:52,460 --> 00:01:56,940
<i>Always so good... wait, 
I don't have time to swoon.</i>

38
00:01:55,750 --> 00:01:57,380
Then, next...

39
00:01:58,220 --> 00:01:59,390
Oh, sorry.

40
00:02:17,070 --> 00:02:19,760
"Quod erat demonstrandum."

41
00:02:19,760 --> 00:02:22,120
That's Latin for "that which 
was to be demonstrated."

42
00:02:22,120 --> 00:02:25,080
In other words,
the proof is concluded.

43
00:02:25,080 --> 00:02:28,040
I don't get it, but that's cool!

44
00:02:28,040 --> 00:02:30,130
<i>Excellent as always...</i>

45
00:02:30,130 --> 00:02:33,300
<i>Did she even factor in that 
the teacher would bump into her?</i>

46
00:02:33,950 --> 00:02:37,620
<i>No, I feel like there was a moment there...</i>

47
00:02:41,380 --> 00:02:42,540
President!

48
00:02:42,540 --> 00:02:44,430
Thank you again!

49
00:02:44,720 --> 00:02:49,020
My boyfriend was super happy
when I gave him that smart watch for his birthday.

50
00:02:49,020 --> 00:02:50,940
Really? That's good to hear.

51
00:02:51,370 --> 00:02:54,860
<i>She even picks out presents 
for her friend's boyfriend?</i>

52
00:02:54,860 --> 00:02:57,070
<i>But that's just like her 
to even get that right.</i>

53
00:02:57,070 --> 00:02:58,730
<i>She's really perf—</i>

54
00:02:58,730 --> 00:03:00,010
But you know what?

55
00:03:00,010 --> 00:03:01,410
The day I gave it to him,

56
00:03:01,410 --> 00:03:03,400
a new version was announced.

57
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:05,160
<i>They announced a new version?!</i>

58
00:03:05,830 --> 00:03:09,120
<i>But she won't just say, 
"Oh, that's too bad."</i>

59
00:03:09,790 --> 00:03:12,470
<i>Yup, there she goes with her ability!</i>

60
00:03:15,420 --> 00:03:21,180
O-Oh, apparently, you can get it
exchanged if you haven't used it yet.

61
00:03:21,180 --> 00:03:22,800
Oh, really?

62
00:03:22,800 --> 00:03:24,580
Thanks again!

63
00:03:24,580 --> 00:03:26,580
<i>Sh-She made a compromise?</i>

64
00:03:26,580 --> 00:03:27,990
<i>What's going on?</i>

65
00:03:28,980 --> 00:03:33,270
<i>After that, she was about to use 
her ability a number of times...</i>

66
00:03:33,730 --> 00:03:36,710
<i>But today, she didn't activate it a single time.</i>

67
00:03:37,630 --> 00:03:40,890
<i>It seemed like she was holding 
herself back from using it,</i>

68
00:03:40,890 --> 00:03:45,350
<i>and it felt like she looked worse 
and worse every time she held back.</i>

69
00:03:45,990 --> 00:03:47,660
Excuse me.

70
00:03:45,990 --> 00:03:48,950
<i></i><i></i><i>Teachers' Office</i>

71
00:03:48,950 --> 00:03:52,190
Phew, made it in time somehow.

72
00:03:53,420 --> 00:03:54,760
President?

73
00:03:57,500 --> 00:03:59,980
President, are you all right?

74
00:03:59,980 --> 00:04:01,220
Shirota-kun?

75
00:04:01,950 --> 00:04:04,810
You were working on the assignments this late?

76
00:04:06,420 --> 00:04:08,990
I guess you really are Slowta-kun.

77
00:04:09,520 --> 00:04:12,860
Never mind me. You don't look so well.

78
00:04:13,590 --> 00:04:16,360
Isn't that because you held back on 
redoing things so many times?

79
00:04:17,240 --> 00:04:19,020
O-Of course not...

80
00:04:24,210 --> 00:04:26,260
I didn't want to redo anything...

81
00:04:27,140 --> 00:04:30,200
This is... a cold...

82
00:04:30,200 --> 00:04:31,830
<i>I was spot on!</i>

83
00:04:32,940 --> 00:04:37,110
<i>But holding herself back 
until she got this bad must be...</i>

84
00:04:37,880 --> 00:04:41,260
<i>because she wanted me to be able 
to focus on my assignments.</i>

85
00:04:42,420 --> 00:04:47,820
Come on, stop holding back and 
undo the entire day so we can redo it!

86
00:04:50,200 --> 00:04:52,810
I-I didn't hold back...

87
00:04:54,120 --> 00:05:01,540
I just... felt like everything 
went perfectly today.

88
00:05:02,130 --> 00:05:03,940
That's why I didn't redo anything.

89
00:05:03,940 --> 00:05:06,660
<i>Your body seems to disagree!</i>

90
00:05:06,660 --> 00:05:09,550
I don't know what you think you sensed,

91
00:05:10,120 --> 00:05:13,830
but it was my own decision
 not to redo anything.

92
00:05:14,140 --> 00:05:16,540
What exactly is the problem with that?

93
00:05:16,540 --> 00:05:21,130
You certainly have a point, but...

94
00:05:21,130 --> 00:05:24,180
If you still insist on having me 
redo something,

95
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:27,340
<i>you</i> take them off.

96
00:05:28,050 --> 00:05:28,710
Huh?

97
00:05:29,930 --> 00:05:30,760
What?!

98
00:05:30,760 --> 00:05:32,560
Wh-What did you expect?

99
00:05:32,560 --> 00:05:35,420
I'm telling you that I am satisfied 
with the current situation,

100
00:05:35,420 --> 00:05:38,650
yet you're insisting that I'm 
somehow overextending myself.

101
00:05:38,650 --> 00:05:41,110
So it's only natural that you take them off.

102
00:05:41,110 --> 00:05:43,940
<i>She never breaks character, huh?</i>

103
00:05:44,350 --> 00:05:46,700
<i>She's being this stubborn because</i>

104
00:05:46,700 --> 00:05:49,950
<i>she wants to support me 
having found some motivation...</i>

105
00:05:49,950 --> 00:05:51,900
<i>That alone is...</i>

106
00:05:52,280 --> 00:05:56,280
Besides, if I made it so 
the entire day didn't happen,

107
00:05:56,280 --> 00:06:01,100
the assignments you worked
 so hard on would be wiped out.

108
00:06:01,100 --> 00:06:02,890
Oh, right.

109
00:06:02,890 --> 00:06:06,510
I'm at a loss for words over
 how unobservant you are.

110
00:06:07,210 --> 00:06:09,340
But that's fine!

111
00:06:11,450 --> 00:06:13,010
Even if they become blank,

112
00:06:13,010 --> 00:06:16,240
I've finished them once already, 
so I think I can get them done quickly.

113
00:06:16,240 --> 00:06:21,180
Besides, I like you the way you usually are.

114
00:06:21,180 --> 00:06:22,560
It's also more reassuring for me.

115
00:06:23,980 --> 00:06:25,620
I-I see.

116
00:06:25,620 --> 00:06:28,640
Well, then... why don't you
 do as you please?

117
00:07:27,950 --> 00:07:28,960
Huh?

118
00:07:28,960 --> 00:07:31,000
I thought we'd be back in the morning.

119
00:07:31,000 --> 00:07:33,060
What are you so confused about?

120
00:07:34,090 --> 00:07:37,000
I thought you undid things?

121
00:07:37,000 --> 00:07:38,350
I did.

122
00:07:38,620 --> 00:07:42,780
I undid the fact that I relinquished 
the decision to redo things to you.

123
00:07:42,780 --> 00:07:43,630
What?

124
00:07:43,630 --> 00:07:45,740
I rethought it right then.

125
00:07:47,570 --> 00:07:51,400
I mean, if I had made it so 
the entire day hadn't happened,

126
00:07:51,880 --> 00:07:55,520
it would have meant that the likes
 of you had made me redo the day.

127
00:07:56,800 --> 00:07:58,870
That is just so...

128
00:08:00,990 --> 00:08:02,340
vexing.

129
00:08:06,170 --> 00:08:09,000
<i>She's got some real pride, huh.</i>

130
00:08:11,020 --> 00:08:14,180
I've got no choice. To ensure this kind 
of thing doesn't happen again...

131
00:08:14,430 --> 00:08:17,180
I will graciously look over them with you.

132
00:08:17,180 --> 00:08:18,100
Huh?

133
00:08:18,100 --> 00:08:20,830
You got additional assignments 
for the summer break, right?

134
00:08:21,580 --> 00:08:25,980
I'm sure, being the bird-brained 
Birdo-kun you are, you've already forgotten.

135
00:08:25,980 --> 00:08:27,260
I didn't forge—

136
00:08:27,260 --> 00:08:29,110
Since I'm sure you will forget,

137
00:08:29,110 --> 00:08:31,200
once summer break starts,

138
00:08:31,200 --> 00:08:33,510
I will teach you one on one.

139
00:08:35,830 --> 00:08:38,300
<i>And then, one day during summer break,</i>

140
00:08:38,300 --> 00:08:41,200
<i>I was in President's room 
while she was helping me</i>

141
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:43,310
<i>with my assignments.</i>

142
00:08:43,940 --> 00:08:46,080
You made a mistake there.

143
00:08:47,090 --> 00:08:49,480
I just taught you that part.

144
00:08:49,480 --> 00:08:51,160
I'm sorry!

145
00:08:51,910 --> 00:08:55,070
You made a mistake again.

146
00:08:55,070 --> 00:08:56,840
Um, ah...

147
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:35,660
I'm giving you personal lessons,

148
00:09:35,660 --> 00:09:37,830
so I expect you to 
solve it perfectly next time.

149
00:09:39,360 --> 00:09:41,950
I guess I'll make some coffee.

150
00:09:41,950 --> 00:09:44,090
Is coffee fine for you as well?

151
00:09:44,090 --> 00:09:45,220
Ah, yes.

152
00:09:45,220 --> 00:09:46,020
Thank you.

153
00:09:46,360 --> 00:09:47,930
If my mother wasn't out,

154
00:09:47,930 --> 00:09:50,750
she could have made us 
a light snack or something.

155
00:09:50,750 --> 00:09:53,200
Is your mother out today?

156
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:55,490
Oh, didn't I mention?

157
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:59,950
My parents have gone on vacation, so they 
won't be back until the day after tomorrow.

158
00:10:00,650 --> 00:10:03,090
I-Is that so...

159
00:10:03,090 --> 00:10:05,780
<i>What am I thinking?!</i>

160
00:10:05,780 --> 00:10:08,040
<i>I'm just here to study.</i>

161
00:10:09,450 --> 00:10:10,600
Shirota-kun.

162
00:10:10,600 --> 00:10:11,290
Yesh?!

163
00:10:11,290 --> 00:10:13,880
You made a mistake in the same place again.

164
00:10:14,220 --> 00:10:15,390
Redo it.

165
00:10:15,390 --> 00:10:16,550
Huh? Wai—

166
00:10:27,080 --> 00:10:28,350
How's your progress?

167
00:10:28,350 --> 00:10:31,570
I'm about halfway done.

168
00:10:31,570 --> 00:10:33,460
Only half?

169
00:10:33,460 --> 00:10:36,040
Now I have to think that you're angling for it.

170
00:10:36,040 --> 00:10:38,070
Angling? What do you mean?

171
00:10:38,590 --> 00:10:41,000
You intentionally go slow 
and sit here until evening,

172
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,020
gradually forcing a sleepover...

173
00:10:43,020 --> 00:10:44,660
Just the two of us at night...

174
00:10:44,660 --> 00:10:46,100
leading to a "shot."

175
00:10:46,100 --> 00:10:47,080
A shot?!

176
00:10:47,500 --> 00:10:50,300
But, unfortunately for you, 
it's not just the two of us.

177
00:10:50,300 --> 00:10:51,880
There is one animal.

178
00:10:51,880 --> 00:10:54,080
So you have a pet?

179
00:10:54,080 --> 00:10:55,380
A cat and you.

180
00:10:55,380 --> 00:10:56,840
<i>I'm a pet to you?!</i>

181
00:10:58,010 --> 00:10:59,730
That's so nice though.

182
00:10:59,730 --> 00:11:02,010
My mother has an allergy, so...

183
00:11:02,010 --> 00:11:04,010
Would it be possible for me to see it?

184
00:11:04,010 --> 00:11:06,930
You wouldn't be able to 
concentrate with an animal in here.

185
00:11:07,950 --> 00:11:11,930
Well, actually, maybe it would help me 
relax and get stuff done better...

186
00:11:13,310 --> 00:11:14,900
Fine, then.

187
00:11:15,370 --> 00:11:18,340
If you say you'll get done quicker, I'll allow it.

188
00:11:18,340 --> 00:11:19,650
Are you sure?

189
00:11:20,680 --> 00:11:23,270
I'm sure she's itching to see you, too.

190
00:11:31,590 --> 00:11:32,740
Sorry for the wait.

191
00:11:32,740 --> 00:11:33,880
Oh, it's fine.

192
00:11:34,760 --> 00:11:38,520
It looks like the cat's gone out to play.

193
00:11:38,520 --> 00:11:41,060
I'm sure it won't be for too long,

194
00:11:41,910 --> 00:11:45,890
It seems I have no choice but 
to be the cat until then.

195
00:11:45,890 --> 00:11:46,850
Why?!

196
00:11:46,850 --> 00:11:51,810
I can't have you using the cat's absence 
as an excuse for not making progress.

197
00:11:51,810 --> 00:11:55,650
B-But I still don't see why you have 
to become the substitute.

198
00:11:56,070 --> 00:12:00,450
I'm going this far for you
and you've still got complaints, meow?

199
00:12:00,450 --> 00:12:01,960
You're already a cat?

200
00:12:05,320 --> 00:12:07,720
<i>I can't focus at all!</i>

201
00:12:07,720 --> 00:12:09,410
<i>What is her goal here?!</i>

202
00:12:09,410 --> 00:12:11,030
<i>Is she just teasing me?</i>

203
00:12:11,030 --> 00:12:15,040
<i>If my assignments take much longer, 
she'll be the one who's inconvenienced...</i>

204
00:12:15,040 --> 00:12:17,750
Ah, I'm so bored.

205
00:12:17,750 --> 00:12:18,960
<i>Oh no!</i>

206
00:12:18,960 --> 00:12:21,250
<i>I'm starting to think 
about all sorts of things!</i>

207
00:12:21,250 --> 00:12:22,930
President!

208
00:12:22,930 --> 00:12:23,970
I'm happy about the gesture, but—

209
00:12:23,970 --> 00:12:24,830
Meow?

210
00:12:24,830 --> 00:12:25,780
Never mind.

211
00:12:26,630 --> 00:12:28,850
<i>She's become more cat than I imagined.</i>

212
00:12:28,850 --> 00:12:33,190
<i>And since I didn't put underwear 
on her after she used her ability...</i>

213
00:12:33,650 --> 00:12:36,080
<i>She's not wearing any! None at all!</i>

214
00:12:34,500 --> 00:12:35,760
Meow.

215
00:12:36,080 --> 00:12:38,270
<i>N-No! Don't picture it!</i>

216
00:12:38,270 --> 00:12:40,690
<i>I won't get anything done on my assignments!</i>

217
00:12:40,690 --> 00:12:43,070
You're not paying attention to me-ow?

218
00:12:43,700 --> 00:12:45,750
Aren't you hearing me-ow?

219
00:12:48,870 --> 00:12:52,810
I'm putting out all the signals here, 
yet you still don't realize.

220
00:12:53,300 --> 00:12:55,190
You really are dense, meow.

221
00:12:56,330 --> 00:12:57,160
<i>Crap!</i>

222
00:12:57,160 --> 00:13:00,300
<i>I'm alone with her and she's 
even more mischievous than usual.</i>

223
00:13:00,300 --> 00:13:01,420
<i>This is...</i>

224
00:13:01,420 --> 00:13:04,300
President! I'm fine now!

225
00:13:04,300 --> 00:13:06,130
I was able to get all the relaxation I needed!

226
00:13:12,310 --> 00:13:13,870
I see.

227
00:13:13,870 --> 00:13:18,840
If that's so, I'll stop 
being a cat for your sake.

228
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:21,120
But.

229
00:13:22,160 --> 00:13:24,250
Since I'm starting to have fun with this,

230
00:13:24,250 --> 00:13:26,750
maybe I'm going to stay 
a cat for a bit longer, meow.

231
00:13:26,750 --> 00:13:29,010
Ahh, please stop it!

232
00:13:29,010 --> 00:13:31,120
These ears are not for listening.

233
00:13:32,730 --> 00:13:37,040
I can't believe it took you this long 
to get a single assignment done.

234
00:13:37,040 --> 00:13:38,890
You really are Slowta-kun.

235
00:13:38,890 --> 00:13:41,750
The last half was because of your interference!

236
00:13:42,160 --> 00:13:45,440
But thank you very much for teaching me.

237
00:13:45,440 --> 00:13:48,290
It seems to be raining. 
Can you make it home?

238
00:13:48,290 --> 00:13:50,430
A little bit of rain should be fine.

239
00:13:50,910 --> 00:13:52,220
Thanks for having me over.

240
00:13:56,340 --> 00:13:58,890
That reminds me that they had 
warnings about torrential rains

241
00:13:58,890 --> 00:14:00,890
from tonight until tomorrow morning.

242
00:14:00,890 --> 00:14:02,630
U-Until morning?

243
00:14:03,100 --> 00:14:07,070
I wouldn't be able to rest easy 
if you were to get into an accident.

244
00:14:08,810 --> 00:14:11,870
It can't be helped. Just stay the night.

245
00:14:12,370 --> 00:14:13,750
<i>Stay the night?!</i>

246
00:14:14,950 --> 00:14:19,960
<i></i><i>Please
 Put Them On, 
Takamine-san</i>

247
00:14:19,960 --> 00:14:24,960
<i></i><i>Please
 Put Them On, 
Takamine-san</i>

248
00:14:25,500 --> 00:14:26,930
I'm sorry...

249
00:14:26,930 --> 00:14:30,550
Really, I'm fine just sleeping 
in the hallway or something.

250
00:14:30,550 --> 00:14:34,640
Doing something that inhospitable 
would make me feel bad.

251
00:14:35,100 --> 00:14:38,220
There's an empty room and bedding for guests,

252
00:14:38,220 --> 00:14:42,060
and you can have some food and use the shower.

253
00:14:42,060 --> 00:14:42,900
If you want,

254
00:14:43,590 --> 00:14:46,470
I could wash your back for you.

255
00:14:46,470 --> 00:14:47,630
Using my body.

256
00:14:47,630 --> 00:14:49,300
That would be too much...

257
00:14:52,390 --> 00:14:54,490
I think the cat's back.

258
00:14:54,880 --> 00:14:56,420
Seems so.

259
00:14:56,420 --> 00:14:58,460
Let me introduce you.

260
00:15:01,630 --> 00:15:03,620
Our house's beloved cat.

261
00:15:03,620 --> 00:15:04,970
Her name's Kuro.

262
00:15:04,970 --> 00:15:06,630
I hope you get along, Shirota-kun.

263
00:15:08,920 --> 00:15:09,980
This cat...

264
00:15:13,260 --> 00:15:15,600
Is so cute!

265
00:15:15,600 --> 00:15:16,860
You like that?

266
00:15:17,600 --> 00:15:18,520
Purr, purr!

267
00:15:18,520 --> 00:15:19,960
Oh...

268
00:15:19,960 --> 00:15:23,190
Not just cute, but such pretty fur.

269
00:15:23,190 --> 00:15:25,650
Is something wrong, President?

270
00:15:27,230 --> 00:15:28,210
Huh?

271
00:15:28,210 --> 00:15:30,410
Was there a lightning strike?

272
00:15:31,960 --> 00:15:34,410
President, are you all right?!

273
00:15:34,890 --> 00:15:36,090
I'm fine.

274
00:15:36,090 --> 00:15:38,540
I'm sure it'll be back on soon,

275
00:15:38,540 --> 00:15:41,370
so let's just pass the time until then.

276
00:15:43,290 --> 00:15:46,350
Why don't you tell me a fun story?

277
00:15:47,870 --> 00:15:48,960
Ready, go.

278
00:15:48,960 --> 00:15:50,350
That's hard!

279
00:15:50,350 --> 00:15:51,840
You're putting me on the spot...

280
00:15:52,250 --> 00:15:54,730
I'll even supply you with a topic, then.

281
00:15:55,480 --> 00:15:56,800
You know...

282
00:15:56,800 --> 00:16:00,360
We've gone to the same grade, 
middle, and high school,

283
00:16:00,360 --> 00:16:05,500
but I really can barely remember 
anything about you from grade school.

284
00:16:05,500 --> 00:16:06,560
Uh-huh...

285
00:16:07,220 --> 00:16:11,230
Tell me something about 
your grade school years.

286
00:16:11,230 --> 00:16:14,500
For instance, fun things you did after school.

287
00:16:15,580 --> 00:16:19,050
Fun things I did after school...

288
00:16:19,050 --> 00:16:20,710
Let's see...

289
00:16:21,540 --> 00:16:24,670
Maybe hanging out at a friend's 
place to play games.

290
00:16:25,130 --> 00:16:27,940
We'd play cooperative multiplayer 
and defeat mons—

291
00:16:27,940 --> 00:16:30,050
That's the first thing that came to mind?

292
00:16:30,050 --> 00:16:32,590
Yeah, I guess so.

293
00:16:35,510 --> 00:16:37,060
It's hot.

294
00:16:37,060 --> 00:16:38,530
Do you want some water?

295
00:16:38,530 --> 00:16:40,310
Th-Thanks.

296
00:16:40,310 --> 00:16:43,980
I guess it's getting hot 
because the AC isn't running.

297
00:16:43,980 --> 00:16:46,350
I'll have a sip first, as well.

298
00:17:04,570 --> 00:17:06,690
I accidentally drank it all.

299
00:17:06,690 --> 00:17:08,500
What kind of accident is that?!

300
00:17:08,850 --> 00:17:10,640
If you want some, go ahead.

301
00:17:10,640 --> 00:17:12,010
From the floor?!

302
00:17:12,330 --> 00:17:14,520
<i>What's going on with her?</i>

303
00:17:14,520 --> 00:17:16,590
<i>Why is she suddenly in such a bad mood?</i>

304
00:17:19,330 --> 00:17:21,180
Any other memories?

305
00:17:21,700 --> 00:17:25,240
<i>They say everyone's got a story to tell, but...</i>

306
00:17:27,080 --> 00:17:29,530
In 4th grade, my nickname was Saito—

307
00:17:29,530 --> 00:17:31,140
Not interested.

308
00:17:32,210 --> 00:17:34,920
<i>Wh-What should I talk about?!</i>

309
00:17:34,920 --> 00:17:39,460
<i>Isn't it unreasonable to be scolding me 
just because my stories aren't fun?</i>

310
00:17:39,460 --> 00:17:41,280
<i>I don't have enough time to think.</i>

311
00:17:41,690 --> 00:17:46,160
I'm getting a bit sweaty. 
May I use your shower?

312
00:17:46,160 --> 00:17:49,120
Sure, give me a moment.

313
00:18:10,920 --> 00:18:14,400
All the towels and body soap are used up,

314
00:18:14,400 --> 00:18:16,580
so you can't use the shower.

315
00:18:16,580 --> 00:18:17,900
I'm sorry.

316
00:18:17,900 --> 00:18:19,990
<i>She did that out of spite?!</i>

317
00:18:23,470 --> 00:18:24,740
<i>I've got no stories.</i>

318
00:18:25,390 --> 00:18:29,710
<i>I can't believe my life has
 been this uninteresting...</i>

319
00:18:29,710 --> 00:18:31,710
<i>I wish I hadn't realized that...</i>

320
00:18:32,370 --> 00:18:35,390
<i>But it looks like she's about to go to sleep?</i>

321
00:18:35,390 --> 00:18:38,680
<i>I guess I don't have to keep 
trying to remember something.</i>

322
00:18:53,230 --> 00:18:56,690
I don't know which year
 in grade school it was...

323
00:18:57,320 --> 00:19:00,410
There was a girl around my age at the park.

324
00:19:00,660 --> 00:19:03,370
We took care of a stray cat there.

325
00:19:04,120 --> 00:19:08,130
I'd take it bits from my school lunch, 
or when it rained...

326
00:19:08,130 --> 00:19:10,120
During a heavy storm like today's...

327
00:19:10,120 --> 00:19:14,090
I rushed over there 
with an umbrella and a towel

328
00:19:14,090 --> 00:19:18,200
but she was already there 
with a huge umbrella and a towel.

329
00:19:22,980 --> 00:19:27,970
Huh. I didn't expect you to have 
a story worth listening to.

330
00:19:27,970 --> 00:19:32,980
But how come you didn't 
bring that story up the first time?

331
00:19:37,130 --> 00:19:38,400
Well...

332
00:20:02,510 --> 00:20:07,180
Even though she'd confessed her feelings to me,
 I wasn't able to give an answer.

333
00:20:07,540 --> 00:20:11,420
At some point, that girl 
stopped coming to the park

334
00:20:11,930 --> 00:20:14,150
and the cat disappeared with her, too.

335
00:20:15,090 --> 00:20:17,570
I do wish I could meet her one more time...

336
00:20:17,570 --> 00:20:21,460
But she didn't speak much, 
so I didn't find out her grade or her name.

337
00:20:22,110 --> 00:20:27,740
Maybe I didn't remember that as a fun 
memory because I have all those regrets.

338
00:20:29,160 --> 00:20:30,210
I see.

339
00:20:30,210 --> 00:20:34,750
So, if you could meet that girl again, 
what would you do?

340
00:20:35,070 --> 00:20:35,830
Huh?

341
00:20:36,950 --> 00:20:38,960
President, are you saying...

342
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:42,880
that you know that girl?!

343
00:20:45,480 --> 00:20:46,490
What?

344
00:20:46,490 --> 00:20:48,050
What's wrong, President?!

345
00:20:50,450 --> 00:20:51,770
Oh well.

346
00:20:54,250 --> 00:20:57,160
I'll give you credit for remembering.

347
00:21:03,310 --> 00:21:06,280
President, the towel! Are you all right?!

348
00:21:06,280 --> 00:21:08,910
What do you mean, "Are you all right?!"

349
00:21:08,910 --> 00:21:12,390
It's almost like you're insinuating 
that I'm in distress or something?!

350
00:21:12,390 --> 00:21:13,870
Please, the towel!

351
00:21:14,460 --> 00:21:17,580
<i>Could it be that she's afraid of lightning?</i>

352
00:21:19,960 --> 00:21:21,630
President?

353
00:21:21,630 --> 00:21:22,670
<i>Maybe...</i>

354
00:21:23,330 --> 00:21:27,340
<i>she was putting all that pressure 
on me and getting carried away,</i>

355
00:21:27,890 --> 00:21:30,690
<i>just so I would take longer with my assignment</i>

356
00:21:30,690 --> 00:21:34,100
<i>all because she's afraid of being alone 
during the thunderstorm?</i>

357
00:21:35,490 --> 00:21:36,500
Shirota-kun.

358
00:21:36,500 --> 00:21:37,310
Y-Yes?!

359
00:21:37,690 --> 00:21:41,310
I'm going to undo that this happened.

360
00:21:41,310 --> 00:21:45,020
But your power doesn't work on me.

361
00:21:45,020 --> 00:21:48,610
Th-Then do everything you can 
to erase it from your memory.

362
00:21:48,610 --> 00:21:49,280
Yes!

363
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:52,200
<i>Thinking back to that day,</i>

364
00:21:52,200 --> 00:21:56,650
<i>I realized that she had 
shown me some vulnerability.</i>

365
00:21:56,650 --> 00:22:00,250
<i>But at the time, I was unable to see that.</i>

366
00:22:02,300 --> 00:22:03,070
President?!

367
00:22:03,070 --> 00:22:04,960
Please don't hold me so tight!

368
00:22:04,960 --> 00:22:07,420
Sheesh! Shirota-kun, do something!

369
00:22:07,420 --> 00:22:09,970
That's insane!

